snippet.textDisplay: Around 5 minutes, Jimmy starts almost to cry. Damn I remember when I heard the news on Sunday. I had my jaw open for 5 minutes straight and just shocked, frozen, paralyzed to my car seat when I was about to head home from a store. Like me, I am sure I am not the only one who felt this way when we heard the news of his death. We will remember where we were last Sunday.   just hope he is resting well, his daughter Gigi and the rest of the 7 people. Whoever they might affect which lives, we dealt with pain (in different variations) and I hope Americans and fans across the global remember how Kobe was, as Mr.Kimmel said. It is not hard on me as much as others, but I still feel the lost. For the bigger fans that knew Kobe more and enjoyed his talent on and off the court, I am dearly sorry for you and I hope you see better days soon. God Rest Us for a better tomorrow and for the families and friends as well.
